{
  "stem": "14724.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of all the countries, large and small, only Great Britain-- which was the smallest of all-- took 10,000 children between 1938 and 1939.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I arrived in June 30, 1939.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But only Great Britain took 10,000 children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, to return to my foster parents-- when a Jewish lady doesn't know what to do with a child-- I think every mother is the same-- they feed it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So she put all this food in front of me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I mean, I hadn't eaten a meal for God knows how long.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A meal-- you know, a meal in the orphanage was sour milk with sugar and cinnamon.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was a meal.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she was very distressed because I just couldn't eat this food, which was so foreign to me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I possibly nibbled on a bread.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I mean, that's about all I could cope with.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I could see her getting more and more upset.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But there was nothing I could do about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Anyway, I think we both gave in, and I went to bed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You have to understand that this lady, at 60-- at 50, had never had children, had no idea how to treat a child.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Next day, my-- I had never been to a hairdresser.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I had never had my hair cut.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my plaits had saved my life many times.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The first thing she did was she took me to a hairdresser and had my plaits cut off.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the second thing she did-- my second name is Kerry.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And in Germany, I had no other name.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I was always Kerry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And she didn't like it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So she decided to choose my other name, which was Ellen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I had never, ever been called Ellen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So every time she called me, I didn't answer.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
